result.name: Genomic Landscape, Evolution and Chemoresistance of Yolk Sac Tumors
result.description: Yolk sac tumors (YSTs) are a major histological subtype of malignant ovarian germ cell tumors, and compared to other subtypes, patients with YST have a worse prognosis. The molecular basis of this disease has not been characterized at the genomic level. Here we characterized 41 clinical tumor samples (and related normal samples) from 30 YST patients, with distinct responses to cisplatin-based chemotherapy.
result.center: Peking Union Medical College Hospital, Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences and Peking Union Medical College
